[{"id": "9363d0c0-07f5-4a61-a5d6-a5e73aa77c4b", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: 1970's british terms/slang for cumming, ejaculating\nASSISTANT: Here's a rundown of British slang for ejaculation that would fit a 1970s setting:\n\n**The acts (verbs):**\n- **Spend / spending** \u2014 Older Victorian term that lingered well into the 20th century; \"I'm going to spend\" was common.\n- **Come off** \u2014 Very common British phrasing; \"make him come off.\"\n- **Get one's rocks off** \u2014 In use by the 70s, slightly American-influenced but well established.\n- **Spill / spill one's lot**\n- **Shoot one's load / shoot off**\n- **Pop off**\n- **Finish** \u2014 Euphemistic, \"are you going to finish?\"\n- **Empty one's bag / empty oneself**\n\n**The substance (nouns):**\n- **Spunk** \u2014 Very British, very period-appropriate; arguably the most authentic 70s term.\n- **Spendings** \u2014 Goes with the verb \"spend.\"\n- **Jism / gism / jizz** \u2014 In circulation, though \"jizz\" feels more late-century.\n- **Spooge** \u2014 More American/later.\n- **Cream** \u2014 \"creaming,\" common.\n- **Seed** \u2014 More literary/euphemistic.\n\n**Most authentically period-British:** *spunk*, *spend/spendings*, *come off*, and *get one's rocks off* will all ring true for a 1970s UK voice. \"Spunk\" in particular is the word that screams British rather than American.\n\nWant me to suggest phrasing for a specific tone \u2014 crude/working-class, posh, or more literary erotica?", "embedding": [-0.05113659054040909, 0.005132609978318214, -0.016447484493255615, 0.013916030526161194, -0.04992201179265976, 0.0037289010360836983, 0.17164911329746246, 0.020537709817290306, -0.03279285132884979, 0.006885215640068054, 0.010307544842362404, -0.008677361533045769, 0.006680590100586414, 0.03137686103582382, 0.008734475821256638, 0.03680318593978882, 0.10799609869718552, -0.031604278832674026, 0.004764757584780455, 0.07985440641641617, 0.07546806335449219, 0.0004338297003414482, 0.00834034848958